descript.abstract: The administrative boundary map shows the political boundaries in the country as defined by laws. The Philippines is divided into three major island groups, namely: Luzon, Visayas, and Mindanao. Together, these areas are further subdivided into 16 regions, and in descending order, a region into provinces, a province into municipalities and cities, and a municipality or city into barangays. The layers or features were acquired from the Natural Resource Atlas Mapscale 1:500,000 dated 1986 and 2000 National Statisttic Office Digital Data.
descript.purpose: DATA DISCLAIMER: At present, there is no official barangay and/or municipal boundary for the whole Philippines. GEODATA derived the Philippine Digital Atlas Dataset from a variety of sources (the 1:500,000 scale Regional Natural Resources Atlas published in 1990 with subsequent bi-annual updates for administrative boundaries, slope, rivers, soil, major roads, land survey, shoreline, climate, land classification, railroad, mineral resources and indigenous layers and the National Statistics Office for the barangay polygons and Census data as of 2000). GEODATA converted these data into a common spatial data format and geographic referencing system. Care was taken in the creation of the various layers, but they are provided "as is". Because GEODATA was not the originator of these databases, we are unable to guarantee the accuracy of their geographic features or attributes. There are no warranties, expressed or implied, including the warranty of merchantability or fitness for a particular purpose, accompanying any of these products.
